  <span id="freeText736410768613773767" style="display:none">Totally agree. I haven't read any other version but I could tell this writer was not competent in telling a story. It was so boring, and his commentaries weren't separated from the text so it confused me (as someone who is not familiar with the story at all). <br /><br />Also, I was told by a Hindu that the Mahabharata is the ultimate scripture on Hinduism (equivalent of the Bible in Christianity or the Koran in Islam) but I didn't find anything in this story which explains the Hindu beliefs about astrology, karma, the five elements, creation, reincarnation, etc. It was just a story about moral values. And in the Mahabharata, they referred to the Vedas as the scriptures. Very confusing overall. Didn't help me to understand Hinduism at all.</span>
